text: The TRT (Turkish Radio and Television Corporation) is the first television broadcaster and national public broadcaster of Turkey. It launched on 1926 as TR (Radio), 1964 May 1th as TRT (Radio), and 1968 January 31 (Television). Currently it has 14 channels.
